The '''Loose Cannon pirates''' were a gang of criminals and mercenaries operating during the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]].

One of their schemes involved entrapping the [[Azzameen family]] with an offer of black-market [[Bacta/Legends|bacta]], then disabling their craft before capturing the family. The purpose of this scheme was unknown, perhaps extortion, or even selling their unfortunate captives into slavery.

However, the Azzameens [[Mission to acquire black market bacta|fought]] their way out of the ambush, destroying several of the Loose Cannon ships in the process. [[Emon Azzameen]] recovered a bottle of [[Zairona Ale]] from the wreckage of the pirate ships, and gave it to his younger brother, [[Ace Azzameen/Legends|Ace Azzameen]], who placed the bottle in his cabin aboard his family's [[YT-2000 light freighter/Legends|YT-2000 light freighter]] ''[[Otana/Legends|Otana]]''.

==Behind the scenes==
The name "Loose Cannon" is speculative, since the actual name of the gang is unknown. However, the briefing in the combat simulation chamber of ''[[Star Wars: X-Wing Alliance]]'' uses this name to refer to the pirate clan.

